---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import BrandBranchesGrid from '../../components/BrandBranchesGrid.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE, MAIN_PHONE_TEL } from '../../data/branches';

const title = "Thermador Stove Repair | Southern California | Star Burner + Pro Grand";
const description = "Thermador stove repair across SoCal, Pro Grand 36/48/60, Pro Harmony 30/36, Star Burner dual-flame, ExtraLow simmer. BSH Irvine CA parts. $89 dx.";
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/thermador-stove-repair/";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Is Thermador the same as Bosch and Gaggenau?",
    a: "All three are <b>BSH Home Appliances</b> brands (Bosch Siemens Hausgeräte, now BSH Hausgeräte GmbH under Bosch Group wholly-owned since 2015). Thermador was acquired by BSH in 1998 as the US luxury appliance brand in the portfolio. Bosch is the mainstream-premium brand globally; Gaggenau is the ultra-luxury Black Forest built-in specialist. Engineering resources are shared but brand platforms and product lines are distinct. Thermador's Star Burner dual-flame design is Thermador-specific; Gaggenau's Vario modular cooktops are Gaggenau-specific. All three share a BSH parts distribution network anchored in the US at the <b>Irvine, California</b> parts warehouse, that's the LA-local advantage: 1-2 day parts for Thermador service vs 5-10 days for most luxury brands that ship from out-of-state. See <a href='/brands/gaggenau-stove-repair/'>Gaggenau stove repair</a> for the BSH sibling."
  },
  {
    q: "What Thermador stove models are most common in LA?",
    a: "Pro Grand Steam dominates LA custom kitchens: PRD364WDHU / PRD484WDHU (36\" and 48\" Dual Fuel with steam+convection oven), PRD486WDHU (48\" Pro Grand Dual Fuel), PRG366WG (36\" Pro Grand all-gas), PRG486WDG (48\" Pro Grand), PRG606WG (60\" Pro Grand six-burner with griddle + grill). Pro Harmony is the narrower-depth pro-style for compact pro-kitchens: PRG305WH (30\"), PRG366WH (36\"). All Pro Grand ship with 2-4 Star Burners + 2-4 ExtraLow simmer burners + griddle / grill module options. BSH Irvine warehouse typically stocks high-movement Pro Grand service parts (igniters, spark modules, burner caps, thermocouples, oven temperature sensors) for 1-2 day LA delivery. Older Pro Grand from 2005-2015 still common in Beverly Hills + Pacific Palisades remodels, parts channel still open through BSH."
  },
  {
    q: "Star Burner flame pattern broken or uneven, what's the usual fix?",
    a: "Thermador's patented Star Burner produces a five-point flame star (vs the conventional ring). When flame pattern breaks: (1) burner cap seating, the Star cap must align with the five flame ports precisely; reseating often free at diagnostic; (2) port obstruction, spillage carbon blocks individual star points; cleaning $160–$240 per burner; (3) orifice verification, propane / NG mismatch common on rental or sold-home installs; orifice swap $180–$280; (4) burner base gasket, heat cycling degrades seal; gasket + reseat $220–$320; (5) gas valve partial restriction; valve swap $300–$440; (6) replacement burner assembly for damaged port geometry $420–$620. Our techs carry Thermador-specific Star Burner caps + orifices in LA dispatch; BSH Irvine warehouse backfills within 1-2 days when assembly-level parts are required. 80% of Star Burner flame-pattern complaints resolve at cap seating + port clean + orifice verification."
  },
  {
    q: "ExtraLow simmer burner not holding low output, what's happening?",
    a: "Thermador's ExtraLow is the lowest residential simmer burner in the category, rated down to ~100°F surface temp with a patented pulse-cycling gas valve that cycles flame on and off rapidly to hold precise low output. When it fails to hold low: (1) pulse-cycle control board, the ExtraLow burner has dedicated cycle logic on the main control board; diagnostic first, board swap $480–$680 when cycle logic confirmed failed; (2) dedicated ExtraLow gas valve, the valve assembly is Thermador-specific, not interchangeable with standard burners; valve swap $340–$480; (3) thermocouple or flame sensor feedback; sensor $220–$320; (4) orifice, ExtraLow orifice sizing distinct from main burners; swap $200–$280; (5) regulator pressure stability. ExtraLow burner service requires Thermador-specific parts, BSH Irvine parts channel standard 1-2 day lead. Rebuilds run 25-30% above standard burner service reflecting the pulse-cycle valve complexity."
  },
  {
    q: "Thermador vs Wolf vs Viking, luxury stove buyer matrix for LA",
    a: "Three reference luxury stove brands in LA custom-kitchen market. <b>Thermador (this page)</b>, BSH German engineering, Star Burner + ExtraLow signature, Irvine CA parts warehouse (LA-local 1-2 day parts advantage). Pro Grand 36/48/60 + Pro Harmony 30/36. <b>Wolf</b>, Sub-Zero Group Madison WI, dual-stacked 20k BTU, Dual Fuel DF signature, coordinated Sub-Zero/Wolf/Cove kitchen-suite. See <a href='/brands/wolf-stove-repair/'>Wolf stove repair</a>. <b>Viking</b>, Middleby Greenwood MS, ProFlow 23k BTU dual-stacked, Brilliance 20+ color program, heritage pro-grade. See <a href='/brands/viking-stove-repair/'>Viking stove repair</a>. Parts networks brand-exclusive. Choice drivers: Thermador for BSH engineering + Irvine parts proximity + ExtraLow simmer precision; Wolf for Dual Fuel + coordinated Sub-Zero/Wolf suite; Viking for pro-grade heritage + color flexibility + highest-BTU signature."
  },
  {
    q: "Pro Grand steam oven not generating steam properly, service approach?",
    a: "Pro Grand Steam is the Thermador signature: a combination steam + convection + conventional oven in the pro-range format (PRD364WDHU, PRD484WDHU). Steam generation depends on: (1) water reservoir + fill-line, clogged or scaled fill path, descale + flush $240–$380; (2) steam generator heating element, dedicated element for the steam cavity, swap $380–$560; (3) steam control-valve assembly, Thermador-specific; swap $460–$660; (4) steam temperature sensor feedback; sensor $240–$340; (5) water-quality filter (in-line), LA hard water drives scale buildup on Thermador steam; filter swap + descale $280–$400 every 18-24 months in LA municipal water. Pro Grand Steam service concentrates in Bel Air + Beverly Hills custom remodels where the steam function is a primary cooking mode. We handle Pro Grand Steam across LA through BSH authorized parts channel."
  },
  {
    q: "Oven igniter glows but convection not heating on Pro Grand Dual Fuel?",
    a: "Pro Grand Dual Fuel combines gas cooktop with electric convection oven. Standard Dual Fuel diagnostic order: (1) convection fan motor, bake + convection depend on airflow circulation; motor swap $340–$500 (Thermador premium vs mass-market equivalent); (2) convection element at rear of oven cavity, element swap $320–$460; (3) bake element, lower element $300–$440; (4) control-board convection-cycle logic, if convection mode not triggering; board swap $480–$680; (5) oven temperature sensor, inaccurate reading affects cycle target; sensor $220–$320; (6) thermal fuse / high-limit safety cutout $240–$340. Igniter glowing but oven not heating on gas-only Pro Grand usually means igniter resistance is out-of-spec (glows but can't reach gas-valve trigger threshold), igniter swap $260–$380 on Thermador pro-range. BSH Irvine parts channel supports 1-2 day component delivery."
  },
  {
    q: "Does the Irvine warehouse actually matter for LA Thermador service?",
    a: "Yes, it's the biggest practical advantage of servicing a Thermador vs most other luxury brands in LA. BSH's <b>Irvine, California</b> distribution center is the US West regional hub for Thermador + Bosch + Gaggenau parts. Typical parts delivery to authorized service in LA: 1-2 days on common service components (igniters, spark modules, burner caps, orifices, thermocouples, temperature sensors). Compare: Viking parts ship from Middleby Greenwood MS (4-6 days typical), Wolf from Sub-Zero Group Madison WI (5-7 days), BlueStar from Prizer-Painter Blandon PA (6-10 days). Where the Irvine advantage shows up: when a household needs stove back online fast for a planned event, Thermador can often be returned to service in 48-72 hours where other luxury brands run 7-10 days. Board-level or specialty-assembly parts (Pro Grand Steam generator, ExtraLow pulse valves) may still run 3-7 days depending on specific item."
  },
  {
    q: "What does Thermador stove repair cost in LA?",
    a: "Residential diagnostic is $89, waived when you authorize the repair. Common Thermador stove bands: Star Burner cap + port clean (per burner) $160–$240; Star Burner orifice swap $180–$280 per burner; burner base gasket + reseat $220–$320; spark-module ignition $280–$400; ignitor tip clean / replace $200–$300; air-mixture adjustment $180–$260; gas-line regulator $220–$320; gas valve swap $300–$440; ExtraLow dedicated gas valve $340–$480; ExtraLow pulse-cycle control board $480–$680 when diagnostic isolates pulse logic; oven igniter $260–$380; bake element (Dual Fuel) $300–$440; convection element $320–$460; convection fan motor $340–$500; temperature sensor $220–$320; thermal fuse / high-limit $240–$340; Pro Grand Steam generator element $380–$560; Pro Grand Steam water-filter + descale $280–$400; control board $460–$660; full replacement Star Burner assembly $420–$620. Thermador service runs 20-30% above mainstream-brand economics reflecting BSH premium parts + diagnostic time, offset partly by the Irvine 1-2 day parts advantage shortening total service window."
  },
  {
    q: "Our Thermador Pro Grand is 12 years old, worth rebuilding?",
    a: "Thermador Pro Grand residential stoves are engineered for 20-25+ year service life on current-generation production. At 12 years, rebuild-vs-replace math strongly favors rebuild: burners, Star Burner assemblies, gas valves, cooktop hardware all serviceable through BSH parts; oven-side electric components (Dual Fuel convection motor + elements) are standard parts; control boards are the one specialty-parts consideration at 10+ years, and BSH typically maintains parts support for 15-20 years on Pro Grand platform. Rebuild economics typical at 12 years: Star Burner refurbishment across all burners (caps + orifices + regulator + air-mix) $700–$1,100; oven-side package (igniter + sensor + convection fan + element service) $900–$1,400; full service-plan assessment $89 diagnostic + quoted labor. Replacement-unit cost for current-production Pro Grand 48\" Dual Fuel runs $12,000–$18,000 retail, rebuild at $1,800–$3,000 is the right economic call in almost all cases for pre-2020 Pro Grand units in sound overall condition."
  }
];

const schemaJsons = [
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "LocalBusiness", "@id": canonical + "#business",
    "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair, Thermador Stove Service",
    "image": "https://samedayappliance.repair/images/same-day-appliance-repair.png",
    "url": canonical, "telephone": MAIN_PHONE_TEL, "priceRange": "$$$$",
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ]
  },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Service", "serviceType": "Thermador Stove Repair",
    "provider": { "@id": canonical + "#business" },
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ],
    "description": "Thermador stove repair across Southern California, LA, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, Riverside. Pro Grand 36/48/60 + Pro Harmony 30/36 + Pro Grand Steam (PRD364WDHU, PRD484WDHU). Star Burner dual-flame signature, ExtraLow pulse-cycle simmer burners, Dual Fuel + all-gas configurations. BSH Hausgeräte Irvine CA parts warehouse (LA-local 1-2 day parts advantage). $89 residential diagnostic waived with repair.",
    "offers": { "@type": "Offer", "priceSpecification": { "@type": "PriceSpecification", "price": "89.00", "priceCurrency": "USD", "description": "Residential diagnostic fee, waived with repair" } }
  },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": faqs.map(f => ({ "@type": "Question", "name": f.q, "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": f.a } })) },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Brands", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Thermador", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/thermador/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 4, "name": "Thermador Stove Repair", "item": canonical }
    ]
  }
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
  <Fragment slot="head-scripts">{schemaJsons.map((schema) => (<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />))}</Fragment>
  <div class="call-banner"><div class="wrap"><span>Thermador stove service? Same-day across all 5 SoCal counties:</span><a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="phone-lg">{MAIN_PHONE}</a></div></div>

  <section class="hero"><div class="wrap">
    <div class="crumb"><a href="/">Home</a> › <a href="/brands/">Brands</a> › Thermador › Stove Repair</div>
    <h1>Thermador Stove Repair</h1>
    <p class="lede">Thermador is the BSH (Bosch Siemens Hausgeräte) US luxury-appliance brand, acquired by BSH in 1998, engineered on BSH's broader German-engineering platform, distributed across the US through the BSH Irvine, California parts warehouse. That Irvine warehouse is the practical advantage most LA households don't realize they're buying: 1-2 day parts delivery into LA authorized service on common Thermador components, where most out-of-state luxury brands run 5-10 days. Pro Grand 36"/48"/60" and Pro Harmony 30"/36" pro-style gas + Dual Fuel stoves anchor the residential lineup; Pro Grand Steam (PRD364WDHU, PRD484WDHU) adds steam+convection oven as the luxury-kitchen cooking-mode flagship. Star Burner dual-flame + ExtraLow pulse-cycle simmer burner are the Thermador burner signatures. Same-day dispatch, $89 residential diagnostic waived with the repair.</p>
    <div class="hero-cta"><a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="btn btn-primary">Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a><a href="#book" class="btn btn-ghost">Request a Visit</a></div>
    <ul class="hero-facts">
      <li><b>BSH Hausgeräte since 1998</b>, Bosch + Siemens + Gaggenau sibling</li>
      <li><b>Irvine CA parts warehouse</b>, 1-2 day LA-local parts delivery</li>
      <li><b>Star Burner + ExtraLow</b>, patented five-point flame + 100°F simmer</li>
      <li><b>$89 residential diagnostic</b>, waived when you authorize the repair</li>
    </ul>
  </div></section>

  <BrandBranchesGrid />

  <section class="trust-bar"><div class="wrap"><span>BHGS #A49573 · Insured</span><span>Same-day in 5 SoCal counties</span><span>Residential diagnostic $89 · waived with repair</span></div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Thermador in LA, BSH engineering + Irvine parts proximity</h2>
    <p>Thermador's US luxury positioning traces back to the 1916 founding in Los Angeles (the original Thermador resistance-heating element shop was on Western Avenue) and stayed a California-anchored brand through the BSH 1998 acquisition. Today Thermador is the US-specific luxury brand in BSH's portfolio: German engineering standards on BSH's broader platform, but product specification and styling matched to US luxury-kitchen design language rather than European apartment scale. Pro Grand 48" and 60" pro-ranges sized for US great-room kitchens; Pro Grand Steam combining steam + convection + conventional oven in a single pro-range chassis unique to the US market.</p>
    <p>Our LA Thermador service geography tracks the BSH Irvine warehouse advantage: most of LA is inside a 1-2 day parts window for common service components, and the Irvine warehouse is a realistic 1-hour drive when same-day parts pickup matters (which it does on emergency Pro Grand Steam service for a household hosting an event). Where Thermador concentrates in LA: Beverly Hills + Bel Air BSH-standard high-end remodels, Pacific Palisades + Brentwood canyon estates, Hollywood Hills architectural custom, Manhattan Beach + Palos Verdes coastal luxury, Pasadena + San Marino established premium, Newport Coast + Corona del Mar OC luxury (Irvine proximity gets even closer to one-hour parts). Households choosing Thermador over Wolf or Viking often weight BSH engineering and Irvine parts proximity heavily in that calculus.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Thermador stove failures our techs see most often</h2>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Star Burner flame-pattern irregularity</h3><p>Patented five-point flame requires precise cap seating + clean ports. Cap reseat often free at diagnostic; port clean $160–$240 per burner; orifice swap $180–$280 on LP/NG mismatch.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>ExtraLow simmer burner not holding low output</h3><p>Pulse-cycle gas valve + dedicated cycle logic on main board. Diagnostic isolates valve vs board. Valve $340–$480; board $480–$680 when pulse logic confirmed failed.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Spark-module ignition degradation</h3><p>Thermador spark module at 8-12 year service. Swap $280–$400. Ignitor tip clean or replace $200–$300 when carbon or electrode wear.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Pro Grand Steam generator, scale in LA hard water</h3><p>LA municipal water drives scale on steam generator + fill-line. Descale + filter $280–$400 every 18-24 months; heating element $380–$560 when element-side fails.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Convection fan motor (Dual Fuel electric oven)</h3><p>Pro Grand Dual Fuel convection depends on airflow. Motor swap $340–$500.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Oven igniter glow-but-no-heat</h3><p>Igniter resistance out-of-spec. Swap $260–$380 on Pro Grand and Pro Harmony oven-side.</p></div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Thermador stove product lines we service</h2>
    <div class="model-grid">
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Pro Grand 36/48/60 (signature)</h3><p>PRG366WG, PRG486WDG, PRG606WG all-gas; PRD484WDHU, PRD486WDHU Dual Fuel; Pro Grand Steam PRD364WDHU + PRD484WDHU.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Pro Harmony 30/36</h3><p>PRG305WH (30"), PRG366WH (36") narrower-depth pro-style for compact pro-kitchens. Star Burner + ExtraLow same spec as Pro Grand.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Star Burner dual-flame</h3><p>Patented five-point flame star (vs conventional ring). 18k BTU signature high-output; all Pro Grand + Pro Harmony.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>ExtraLow pulse-cycle simmer</h3><p>Down to ~100°F surface temp via pulse-cycling gas valve. Lowest residential simmer in category. Dedicated valve + cycle logic.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Pro Grand Steam</h3><p>Steam + convection + conventional oven in pro-range format. Unique to Thermador US market. Requires periodic descale in LA hard water.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Dual Fuel configurations</h3><p>Gas cooktop + electric convection oven. Overlaps with Thermador range line. Standard on 48"/60" Pro Grand luxury builds.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Thermador vs Wolf vs Viking, luxury buyer matrix</h2>
    <p><b>Thermador (this page)</b>, BSH Hausgeräte, Star Burner + ExtraLow signature burners, Irvine CA parts warehouse LA-local 1-2 day advantage. Pro Grand 36/48/60 + Pro Harmony 30/36. Parts through BSH Irvine regional hub.</p>
    <p><b>Wolf</b>, Sub-Zero Group Madison WI, dual-stacked 20k BTU, Dual Fuel DF signature, coordinated Sub-Zero/Wolf/Cove kitchen-suite integration. Parts ship 5-7 days from Madison. See <a href="/brands/wolf-stove-repair/">Wolf stove repair</a>.</p>
    <p><b>Viking</b>, Middleby Greenwood MS, ProFlow 23k BTU, heritage pro-grade + Brilliance color program. Parts ship 4-6 days from Greenwood. See <a href="/brands/viking-stove-repair/">Viking stove repair</a>.</p>
    <p>Choice drivers that show up in real LA service: Thermador for BSH engineering + Irvine parts proximity + ExtraLow simmer precision; Wolf for coordinated Sub-Zero/Wolf/Cove suite integration + Dual Fuel Fan; Viking for pro-grade heritage + color-program flexibility + highest-BTU output. Parts networks brand-exclusive, no cross-reference. See also <a href="/brands/gaggenau-stove-repair/">Gaggenau stove repair</a> for the BSH sibling.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>What Thermador stove repair typically costs</h2>
    <table class="price-table">
